But Indurain, just one week before the Tour of Italy, refused to give  Rominger a psychological edge by immediately responding in kind, winning the  Tour de l'Oise at Senlis in France.
He wrapped up the four-stage event by winning a final 12km time trial,  averaging 47.937km to edge out Frenchman Eddy Seigneur by 5secs and Britain's  Chris Boardman, the former world one hour record holder, by 12.
